    • getWhenUpToOneRBMapIsNonEmpty

      @SafeVarargs public static <K,​ V> java.util.Optional<RBMap<K,​V>> getWhenUpToOneRBMapIsNonEmpty​(RBMap<K,​V> first, RBMap<K,​V> second, RBMap<K,​V>... rest)
      If all maps are empty, returns an empty map. If only one is non-empty, returns the non-empty one. Otherwise returns Optional.empty(). This is useful for set unions; if this returns a non-empty optional, it means it's a valid result of a set union. It can speed up set union calculations in those special cases.
